can also be hard on those plants most dependent upon water the irrigation crew makes sure campus flora stays well watered while our shrub crews work to prune spring growth visit our summer page for more information on what we re up to campus blooms summer specimens of interest month by month gardening tips back to top fall as the weather begins to chill trees and plants around campus change their color and leaves scatter across the grounds both nature and nurture are actively changing the landscape as grounds personnel gear up for the approaching winter visit our fall pages for more information on what we re up to campus blooms fall specimens of interest month by month gardening tips fall color plants and locations fall walking tours back to top winter the autumn chill turns quickly into winter storms some plants may be dormant while others take advantage of the rain to grow grounds crews spring into action keeping the campus clean after every storm visit our winter page for more information on what we re up to campus blooms winter specimens of interest month by month gardening tips back to top weather and forecast daily changes in weather can impact life across the campus from trees and shrubs to students and faculty grounds utilizes the following tools to help us better care for the campus and its many residents staff and visitors the weather station allows our sprinkler systems to water just the right amount back to top seasons spring seasons summer seasons fall seasons winter seasons spring stanford university all rights reserved stanford ca 94305 drupal site designed and developed by wired moon in partnership with lbre
